row and measured\n56 degrees seen from Earth. In most cases, only CME halos and partial halos,\nlead to severe geomagnetic storms. We performed a cross-check analysis of the\nFD events detected during the rise phase of the current solar cycle 24, the\ngeomagnetic parameters, and the CACTus CME catalog. Our study suggests that\nnarrow angular-width CMEs that erupt in the western region of the ecliptic\nplane can lead to moderate and severe geomagnetic storms.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 14 May 2018 16:43:08 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Tue, 15 May 2018 20:05:09 GMT"}],"update_date":"2018-05-17"}
