ha=(5,6,\\cdots,d)$, and gauge fields, those with the space\nindex $\\alpha=(0,1,2,3)$. While states of the Lorentz group and all its\nsubgroups (in any dimension) are in Clifford space in the fundamental\nrepresentations of the groups, with the family degrees of freedom included,\nstates in Grassmann space manifest with respect to the Lorentz group adjoint\nrepresentations, allowing no families.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 15 May 2018 12:02:27 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Thu, 17 Jan 2019 12:33:48 GMT"}],"update_date":"2019-01-18"}
